&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;When is this worth it?&lt;/strong&gt; Run the computation in the Profiler and check its self-time. If it's consistently over 1-2ms and the component re-renders frequently, &lt;code&gt;useMemo&lt;/code&gt; is justified. For simple operations like filtering a 10-item array, the memoization overhead often costs more than it saves.&lt;/p&gt;




&lt;h2&gt;


Step 5: Fix Category C — Long Lists
&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Never render 10,000 DOM nodes. The browser can't handle it, and neither can React's reconciler.&lt;/p&gt;

